  "texts": [
    "Obviously, for the prediction of the i-th tool/strategy, the best performing algorithm/ setup for that tool/strategy will be run.",
    "The average weighted accuracy achieved globally and singularly for the tools and the strategies is reported in Table 5, jointly with the standard deviation, the minimum and the maximum of the results and the average F1-score.",
    "The weighted accuracy in predicting the tool and the strategies is around 90% in average (88.7% for the former and 91.6% for the latter) and, globally, 90.4% is achieved, with a low standard deviation of 0.079 and 0.088 for tools and strategies, respectively, and 0.084 globally).",
    "Thus, the implemented algorithm is capable to output around 9 correct predictions each 10 about the most useful support methodologies for university students with dyslexia, based on the issues they encountered.",
    "The good result is confirmed by the F1-score, which is 0.927 for the tools, 0.945 for the strategies and 0.938 in general."
